up with peoples cleancut young performers have 
sung and danced their way around the world many times since 1965 
this week thousands of alumni are gathering to celebrate the 
organizations 25th anniversary 
j blanton belk founded the musical goodwill troupe in an effort 
to channel the idealism of the young and spread an upbeat message 
of universal brotherhood during a disruptive era of civil rights 
marches antiwar protests and political assassinations 
it was a very young world that wanted to have a say in what 
happened to them much more so than past generations recalled 
belk a former navy officer 
since then some 11000 up with people troubadours have 
performed in virtually every country 
more than 5000 alumni from 41 countries are expected to attend 
a fourday celebration including concerts and slide shows that 
opens wednesday at the colorado convention center the organization 
takes on about 650 people aged 18 to 26 each year 
president and mrs bush serve as honorary cochairmen for the 
event but were not expected to attend said spokesman julie 
hammerstein said a cast of up with people performed at bushs 
inauguration last year 
