to fulfill their missions assigned by the zionists and western 
spying agencies 
the article which was obtained by the associated press in 
cyprus blamed officials of the ministry of islamic guidance which 
is in charge of regulating the activities of foreign reporters for 
giving reporters too much freedom on their trips to iran 
journalists who visit iran are assigned agents from the ministry 
who accompany them on all trips outside their hotels reporters are 
also required to submit their film and tapes to ministry officials 
for approval 
it is simplicity if we think that the cia the israeli 
mossad and other intelligence services simply use one device to 
obtain information from iran the newspaper said in addition 
to their set formula they send reporters photographers and 
cameramen as a coverup 
the iranian government allows few western news organizations to 
base representatives in iran and other reporters are allowed to 
visit the country only on special occassions recently reporters 
were allowed in to cover the first anniversary of the death of 
irans spiritual leader ayatollah ruhollah khomeini and the june 
