the world press freedom committee is urging 
all organizations hoping to foster a free press in eastern europe 
to coordinate their efforts through a meeting in october 
an entirely new dimension of needs and opportunities faces all 
of us harold w andersen chairman of the committee and former 
publisher of the omaha worldherald said july 17 we all need to 
know what is being done and not being done 
he urged interested organizations to take part in a oneday 
conference at the national press club in washington on oct 10 
the 14yearold committee which represents 33 national and 
international news organizations from five continents already has 
surveyed the media of eastern europe and has prepared a list of 
possible projects 
