wfbq advising it of the fine 
the fcc found that portions of five broadcasts of the bob and 
tom show aired between june 1987 and august 1989 contained lewd 
and vulgar language dwelling on depictions or descriptions of 
sexual organs and activities 
the station was fined the maximum 2000 for each violation the 
station has 30 days to appeal or to pay the fine 
chris wheat station manager said a decision would be made in a 
few days on whether the ruling would be appealed 
wfbq had argued that the routines were at most indirect 
nonexplicit doubleentendre humor about sexual matters 
however the fcc ruled that the language used in each passage 
was understandable and clearly capable of a specific sexual meaning 
and because of the context the sexual import was inescapable 
in june the fcc imposed a 20000 fine against ksjofm of san 
jose calif for indecent broadcasts 
