legal ethics 
it is 7 pm as drinan surveys his class gathered in seven rows 
of desks before him in a large room walled with concrete blocks 
painted blue four large television sets are suspended from the 
ceiling but they are silent and drinan speaks without competition 
legal ethics 
anyone who says that legal ethics is an oxymoron a 
contradiction in terms will have to leave the room drinan had 
joked earlier 
but now hes asking questions 
does a lawyer have an obligation to report on his fellow 
lawyers when he sees something wrong 
he tells of a lawyer in chicago who was suspended for a year 
caught between the competing demands of the attorneyclient 
privilege and the obligation to report another lawyers wrongdoing 
was there an injustice drinan asks his students should 
he have gone to jail had his finger cut off or what 
drinan moves out from behind the lectern paces hands shoved 
deep in his pockets continuing the lecture in a strong raspy 
voice 
theres a lawyer in new york who represents the bad lawyers 
he seems to enjoy this line of work maybe youll get into legal 
ethics as a career after this midsummer nights dream 
no 
drinan scrawls case citations and legal rules on a blackboard 
