he was called a political prodigy an 
eloquent spokesman for the young israeli nation now he feels the 
jewish state he so strongly defended has taken a wrong turn but 
abba eban at 75 has no real political power now and he vents his 
frustrations mainly through the media 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the cultured cambridgeaccented wit and oratory 
of abba eban once was the voice of israel extolling the young 
nations virtues before the world and defending it from attack by 
its enemies 
the voice has been muted for some time now and when eban at 75 
does speak up he is more likely to admonish than praise the israel 
that has grown up in the past 42 years 
the tall stately former ambassador and politician is saddened 
by what he sees as a besmirched image of israel stemming from the 
incessant conflict with the palestinians in the occupied lands 
i think there is a sense of a paradise lost he says 
there is a kind of broken heart especially among jews about the 
