in the 1860s and 1870s russian czarist forces subjugated the 
central asian regions of turkestan and khiva and the cities of 
tashkent samarkand and bokhara after the 1917 russian revolution 
the territories were reorganized as five soviet republics 
here is a brief look at the history people land and economies 
of the central asian republics 
</TEXT>
