war and peace an opera based on tolstoys 
epic novel of five families during the russian victory over 
napoleon in 1812 is hitting a high note of musical glasnost 
even the final scene was redesigned for the 21 million 
production of sergei prokofievs rarely performed extravaganza 
tops among a series of sovietamerican performing arts ventures in 
seattle in conjunction with the goodwill games this summer 
stage director francesca zambello said initial plans called for 
the victorious gen kutuzov to arrive in a tank as soldiers and 
peasants wave red flags reflecting the soviet triumph over the 
nazis after the opera was written in 1942 
when the berlin wall came down thats when we decided were 
going to have to change this she said 
instead kutuzov walks onstage as more of a partisan a sort 
of man of the people and red army trappings have been dropped in 
favor of a broad stroke about people being freed from 
oppression she said 
with nearly three dozen singers in 69 roles an 80member 
chorus more than 100 supernumeraries and 80 musicians war and 
peace is the biggest project yet for the seattle opera which 
gained international prominence with annual performances of richard 
wagners der ring des niebelungen 
the seattle opera became a mecca for wagner fans with annual 
ring performances from 1975 to 1987 the longest run anywhere 
outside the composers old home in bayreuth germany 
its amazingly cast said soprano sheri greenawald who 
sings natasha its like francesca was saying yesterday the 
people are who they are cast 
