<TEXT>
the united auto workers union and the nations 
big three automakers have given few clues about how labor 
negotiations will progress during the next eight weeks 
the uaw opened talks with general motors corp on wednesday 
with ford motor co on thursday and with chrysler corp on friday 
the contracts expire sept 14 
there were no surprises in the three opening days of bargaining 
and there arent likely to be any in the next few weeks beginning 
today negotiating committees break up into subcommittees focusing 
on specific areas including job security overtime and healthcare 
benefits and costs 
at news conferences after the opening day of talks at each of 
the automakers union and management officials spoke mostly about 
general concepts except for chrysler chief negotiator anthony st 
john 
chrysler the company which could be hurt the most in this round 
of talks said it proposed setting up a multiemployer healthcare 
trust like the other automakers chrysler has said it will be 
seeking relief from the soaring costs of health care for its active 
and retired employees 
but unlike the others so far in the talks chrysler outlined a 
method designed to do that and chrysler isnt limiting membership 
in the plan to the automakers 
st john said chrysler would consider hooking up with all sorts 
of industries in the health plan with a larger group the plan 
would have more clout with insurers and costs could be driven down 
he also said formation of such a trust would get around a change 
in accounting rules in 1993 st john said the change which would 
require employers to set aside money in benefit programs instead of 
paying as they go could add 7 an hour to its labor costs 
so far gm and ford have been cool to the idea 
chrysler and wall street analysts said chryslers secondquarter 
earnings should be about half of last years 341 million the 
company is expected to lose a considerable amount of money in the 
third quarter when two of its most profitable plants close for 
retooling 
shrinking profits car and truck sales running 13 percent behind 
last years pace at the end of last month and the companys 
