<TEXT>
kansas city power and light co made an 
857 million tender offer for kansas gas and electric co monday a 
move kcpl officials said would cut costs for both utilities and 
delay their need to add generating capacity 
kcpl executives say they could freeze rates for all customers 
until jan 1 1993 if the merger goes through 
the offer for 27 in cash per common share would be financed 
by a 1 billion credit agreement that kcpl has signed with two 
banks westpac banking corp and the first national bank of 
chicago company officials said 
the share price offered is 37 percent more than kgampes stock 
price friday according to kcpl kgampe stock which closed at 1975 
friday closed at 2437 monday on the new york stock exchange 
while kcpls stock fell 87 cents to close at 3150 
at least 90 percent of kgampes shares must be offered the tender 
offer also requires approval of state and federal regulators kcpl 
officials said 
the only comment i can make is we have received the offer we 
will evaluate it we will respond after that evaluation is 
complete said lyle koerper a kgampe spokesman in wichita 
koerper said he did not know when the evaluation would be 
complete 
the offer is scheduled to expire at midnight aug 20 
in a letter to kgampe officials kcpls president and chief 
executive a drue jennings said the merger would make more 
complete and efficient use of kgampes generating capacity and delay 
kcpls need to add capacity 
at a news conference jennings said for several years he has 
discussed the merger idea informally with wilson cadman kgampe 
president and board chairman 
jennings described mondays tender offer as a nudge 
our companies are very good friends he said theyve done 
a lot of commercial business together over the past 25 years i 
think its a good deal i really do 
kcpl also filed a federal lawsuit monday seeking a court order 
requiring kgampe to comply with a kansas law that would require it to 
call a special shareholders meeting within 30 to 50 days the 
meeting would be to authorize kcpl to vote all of the shares it 
acquires through its tender offer 
jennings said his company proposes to expand its board of 
directors by five members to add representatives from kgampes 
service headquarters and to add a citizens advisory commission to 
represent consumers in kgampes service territory 
jennings said he was optimistic that both kgampe and regulators 
would be receptive to the offer 
i think theyll appreciate what they see he said this is 
a strategic combination that really does make sense it probably 
should have been done years ago 
kcpl has about 409000 customers in 23 counties in western 
missouri and eastern kansas including the kansas city area it has 
about 2800 employees 
kgampe serves about 254000 customers in southeastern kansas 
including the wichita area it employs about 1330 
kcpl said it plans no layoffs if the merger goes through 
the two utilities each own 47 percent of the wolf creek nuclear 
power plant in southeast kansas kansas electric power cooperatives 
inc owns the remainder 
jennings said the merger would not affect the hybrid corporation 
that runs wolf creek or the plants daytoday operations 
</TEXT>
