said the federal reserve boards recent moves to lower interest 
rates have been a boon to the gold market 
it looks like some foreigners are concerned about the 
possibility that fed chairman alan greenspans stance toward 
inflation may be weakening which pulled the props out from under 
the dollar savaiko said 
