northwest airlines chairman wants to oversee 
a controlled sale of eastern airlines assets and buy many of 
easterns planes and gates in atlanta according to a published 
report 
the story in mondays editions of the wall street journal said 
the proposal was expected to be made monday but eastern said it 
had received no offer from northwest to buy parts of the airline 
the newspaper reported that northwest chairman alfred a checchi 
was expected to make the proposal to eastern and its creditors the 
journal reported the plan would call for northwest to take over 
certain eastern assets including 80 of easterns newer aircraft 
airport gates in atlanta and maintenance facilities in atlanta and 
miami 
