oil giant exxon corp said monday its secondquarter profit 
soared nearly sevenfold from a year ago when it set aside a 
special provision to handle the massive cleanup from the oil spill 
in valdez alaska 
meanwhile atlantic richfield co reported a 16 percent drop in 
quarterly earnings amoco reported a 23 percent decline for the 
second quarter and amerada hess corp reported a 721 million net 
loss ashland oil inc said net income for its fiscal third quarter 
more than doubled 
