in the three months ended june 30 compared with earnings of 140 
million or 11 cents a share in the 1989 quarter revenue totaled 
2608 billion up 10 percent from 2361 billion a year ago 
last years results included an 850 million provision for the 
valdez spill without that exxon said it would have earned 990 
million or 78 cents per share in the 1989 quarter 
