computer problems at the associated press 
resulted in transmission of incomplete stock options tables monday 
a problem in computer programs that process incoming trading 
data resulted in some transactions being excluded from the tables 
said john reid ap vice president and director of communications 
and technology 
it could not be immediately determined how many transactions 
were missing he said 
the situation was compounded because the tables couldnt be 
checked until computers had finished processing them which took 
three hours longer than normal because of the computer glitch 
reid said the problem did not affect any other stocks tables 
produced by ap 
the problem was corrected and tuesdays stock options tables 
would be complete he said 
