<TEXT>
charles schwab amp co inc was fined 
375000 and censured after a new york stock exchange investigation 
of trading practices by schwabs reorganization department company 
officials announced 
from january 1985 through september 1988 the department which 
processes tender and exchange offerings stock purchase rights and 
warrants and convertible redeemable securities would sometimes 
submit more securities than it had instructions from the customer 
to tender according to a company statement issued monday 
the trading practices sometimes resulted in gains for schwab 
the statement said when gains occurred schwab disbursed the 
related net credits with interest to affected customer accounts 
the nyse hearing panel found that the department had acted 
principally to avoid losses when the firm received and honored late 
customer instructions and to protect against errors in complex 
junkbond transactions according to the statement 
in addition to the fine two employees have been censured the 
company said 
we have undertaken strong internal measures to prevent such 
practices in the future including new policies governing each type 
of reorganization transaction separation of functions and a 
complete restructuring of the reorganization department said 
charles r schwab founder and chairman 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

